text.section:
On or before October 1 of each year, and every 6 months thereafter, the Board of Trustees shall submit a report in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article to the Senate Budget and Taxation Committee, the House Appropriations Committee, and the Joint Committee on Pensions that provides:
a summary of correspondence with companies engaged by the Board of Trustees under this section;
all divestment actions taken by the Board of Trustees in accordance with this section;
a list of companies doing business in Iran or Sudan which the Board of Trustees has determined to be ineligible for investments of net new funds under subsection (d)(2) of this section; and
other developments relevant to investment in companies doing business in Iran or Sudan.
